The paper deals with the complexity of distinguishing between two quantum circuits, which is a fundamental problem in quantum computing. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.QI (Quantum Information) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the problem in the context of physical processes, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper uses techniques from machine learning, which could make it relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
